text.tspan: The Global Living Planet Index (LPI) measures the average decline in monitored wildlife populations. The index
value is measured relative to 20,811 populations of 4,392 species in 1970 (i.e. 1970 = 100%).
Source: World Wildlife Fund (WWF) and Zoological Society of London
Note: 95% upper and lower confidence intervals are shown in grey.
